# Workflow builder feature context

Full reference: **[docs/workflow-builder.md](docs/workflow-builder.md)** (SDK contracts, LLM pipeline, query builder, builder UI, data model, API, Phase 3 roadmap).

Summary: user prompts generate sandboxed JavaScript via OpenAI. SDK types in `workflow-sdk.ts` are injected into the LLM system prompt as compiler instructions. Generic `QueryOptions` pattern powers data tools (`getSessions`, `getMessages`). Workflows subscribe to multiple triggers via `trigger_events TEXT[]`. Builder UI is a split-pane (prompt panel + shiki code viewer). Execution: **E2B** sandboxes; a trusted **workflow harness** builds stub `tools` and invokes `run(event, tools)` — see `docs/workflow-builder.md`.

Consider these rules if they affect your changes.
